  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my LESCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit LESCO reference number in the bill checker tool at the top of this page and click Check Bill. Your complete LESCO electricity bill for March 2026 appears on screen within seconds — showing the amount due, due date, units consumed, and all charges. This is free, requires no login, and works 24 hours a day." },
    { question: "What is the 14-digit LESCO reference number and where is it?", answer: "Your LESCO reference number is a permanent 14-digit number that uniquely identifies your connection. It is printed in bold on the top-right corner of every LESCO electricity bill, just above the barcode. It is also printed on the payment slip at the bottom of the bill. If you have lost all previous bills, call LESCO helpline 118 with your CNIC and registered address to retrieve it." },
    { question: "Can I check my LESCO bill by Customer ID instead of reference number?", answer: "Yes. Click the 'Customer ID' tab in the checker above and enter your 10-digit Customer ID. Your Customer ID is printed below your name on the LESCO bill, usually labeled 'Customer No.' or 'Consumer ID.' Both methods pull the exact same complete bill from the PITC server." },
    { question: "How do I download my LESCO bill as a PDF?", answer: "After your LESCO bill appears in the checker above, click the 'Download PDF' button. Your browser opens the print dialog — select 'Save as PDF' as your printer destination and click Save. Your LESCO duplicate bill saves as a PDF file instantly. You can then share it by WhatsApp, email, or print it at any shop." },
    { question: "How do I get my LESCO bill via SMS?", answer: "Type pitc followed by a space and your 14-digit LESCO reference number, then send to 8334. For example: pitc 12345678901234. You receive your current bill amount, due date, and units consumed as an SMS reply within seconds. Standard SMS charges apply." },
    { question: "Why is my LESCO bill so high this month?", answer: "Several factors can spike a LESCO bill: (1) Increased AC usage in summer adds 200–500 units per month; (2) A high Fuel Price Adjustment (FPA) set by NEPRA this month; (3) You crossed from Protected to Unprotected status — meaning your 6-month average exceeded 200 units; (4) Someone tampered with your meter or wiring; (5) Meter reading error by LESCO staff — check if 'Estimated' appears on your bill instead of 'Actual.' For estimated bills, request an actual meter reading." },
    { question: "What are LESCO peak hours and how do I avoid high charges?", answer: "LESCO summer peak hours are 6:30 PM to 10:30 PM (April–October). Winter peak hours are 6:00 PM to 10:00 PM (November–March). Electricity costs more per unit during these windows. To save money, run your AC, washing machine, iron, and electric geyser before 6 PM or after 11 PM. Just shifting these three appliances outside peak hours reduces most Lahore household bills by Rs 200–500 per month." },
    { question: "How do I pay my LESCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, HBL, MCB, Meezan Bank, or any bank mobile app. Open the app, go to Bill Payments, select Electricity, choose LESCO, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify the amount, and confirm. You receive an instant SMS confirmation. You can also pay at any JazzCash or Easypaisa retail shop in Lahore by giving your reference number to the agent." },
    { question: "What is the LESCO grace period for bill payment?", answer: "LESCO gives consumers 7 days after the due date printed on the bill to pay without a late payment surcharge. After the 7-day grace period, a 10% late payment surcharge applies to the total unpaid amount. For example, on a Rs 5,000 bill, paying after the grace period costs you an additional Rs 500. Always pay on or before the due date to avoid this penalty." },
    { question: "How do I check my LESCO load shedding schedule?", answer: "Visit ccms.pitc.com.pk and enter your 14-digit LESCO reference number in the search box. Click Search. Your specific feeder's complete load shedding schedule appears — showing exactly which hours your area has no electricity each day. Areas with higher bill payment rates receive priority supply under LESCO's feeder-wise load management policy." },
    { question: "How do I file a complaint about my LESCO bill?", answer: "Call LESCO helpline 118 or 0800-00118 with your 14-digit reference number ready. Describe the issue clearly and get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN). If unresolved within 14 working days, escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 (toll-free) or file online at nepra.org.pk. Under NEPRA regulations, LESCO is legally required to respond to billing complaints within this timeframe." },
    { question: "How do I apply for a new LESCO connection?", answer: "Apply online at lesco.gov.pk under Online Services → New Connection, or visit your nearest LESCO office. You need your CNIC, property ownership or tenancy documents, and a site plan. Standard domestic connections (5 kW) take 15–30 working days. You can also apply through the national new connection portal at enc.com.pk by selecting LESCO as your DISCO." },
  ]}

